column5: I was also a little dissapointed, as it looked like a good show.  However, I believe there are 2 different history channels I think there is the "History Channel" and there is "History Television" one being Canadian and one being American.  This show was obviously in the US.  This happened with another series they aired last year called Ice Road Truckers about truckers driving the ice roads up north.  I managed to get those off of a bit torrent site, so I would assume this one would be there also.  Andrew.
http://www.history.com/minisites/life_after_people   Should be an interesting show.  G
Thanks gerritt,i just programed the vcr...thats going to be a good show,i watch the history channel all the time man thanks for letting us know bud !!....cheers
They have been advertising it here also Gerritt, my favorite channel. A lot of good programs.
How would that be considered history? It's a show about the future, no?? Still, it looks interesting.
Thanks Gerritt. that is a good show. i will be sure to watch it. question for you Gerritt- do you remember who i am?   Dann
I love the line " How would you survive?" Duh! The caption reads population 0 (ZERO)!!! That means no survivors, right?
Uhmmmmmm........ no?  G
I see no reason to watch it, there'll be nothing but Cockroaches and Ants left...
What worries me is, who's manning the cameras!
With the way some of the worlds wackos are acting lately, it may not be too much longer till were ALL history anyways.....including the wackos.
History channel rocks!  Discovery channel too.  Thanks for the heads up.
Hey Gerritt------ if i was wearing my jacket with the reflective stripes on it and standing beside Tracker, i bet you would remember..--lol we were at the G2G with every one else.
Ohhhh Yeah man hey!!! That was good times! cold but good! doing any ice fishing this winter?  G

well if mother nature starts to do her job then yes i will be out. i think shes starting now. lets hope she keeps up the good work. not sure where my hut is going on simcoe but if you see it stop by and say high.   Dann

I'm on Rogers in  Pickering, can anyone tell me what the channel is supposed to be. I see a show called "Rome" on the History channel tomorrow at 9:00. Looked up and down the channels but couldn't seem to find it. Looks like a very interesting show though.  SS
its called "LIFE AFTER PEOPLE " JAN 21ST @9 PM THATS ALL I CAN TELL YOU. HOPE IT HELPS.   Dann

I am on Rogers in Scarborough at Port Union Rd.  I get the History channel on 54, I would assume that it is the same number in Pickering.  It may also be available on another number in HD if you have a digital box.

Sounds cool, I read a book a few months ago called The World Without Us, which is also about what the world would be like if we disappeared, e.g., how long before all the buildings crumble, what animal species would bounce back...  Mike

Sounds like a good show though.  BTW, in that clip, the shot with the payphone off the hook was taken in Quebec. If you turn up the volume you can just hear the Walmart employee saying "for service in French, press 9. Your call is important to us."
The Omega Man?
for service in French, press 9. Your call is important to us." LOL Roy, come to the US we can probably fit you in at number 3? You might have to bid on the spot though?
I couldnt find it either we have Bell expressvue and Rome was on too
Same here... what gives? I bet the CRTC is behind this...   <_<
